'''Sir John Fitzgerald''' (1857 &ndash; 2 November 1930) was an [[Ireland|Irish]]-born [[United Kingdom|British]] [[brewer]] and wine and spirit merchant<ref>Biography, ''[[Who Was Who]]''</ref> who served as [[Lord Mayor]] of [[Newcastle upon Tyne]] from 1914 to 1915. Born in [[County Tipperary|Tipperary]], he was [[Knight Bachelor|knighted]] in the 1920 New Year Honours for his services to Newcastle.<ref>{{London Gazette |issue=31712 |date=30 December 1919 |page=2 |supp=y}}</ref> He founded the Sir John Fitzgerald pub chain<ref>[http://www.sjf.co.uk/about/history.php Sir John Fitzgerald website] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120615140104/http://www.sjf.co.uk/about/history.php |date=2012-06-15 }}</ref> that bears his name and is still owned and operated by his descendants.
