Because [[diplomatic mission]]s, such as embassies and consulates, may not be entered by the host country without permission (even though they do not enjoy [[extraterritoriality|extraterritorial status]]), persons have from time to time taken refuge from a host-country's national authorities inside the embassy of another country.

