'''St Leger St Leger, 1st Viscount Doneraile''' (born St Leger Aldworth; died 15 May 1787), was an [[Anglo-Irish]] politician and peer. 

[[File:Doneraile Court - geograph.org.uk - 1392610.jpg|thumb|Doneraile Court - seat of the Viscounts Doneraile]]
==Life and career==
He was the son of Richard Aldworth and the Hon. [[Elizabeth Aldworth|Elizabeth St Leger]].<ref name="Brydges1817p271">{{cite book |first=Egerton |last=Brydges |title=A biographical peerage of Ireland, in which are memoirs and characters of the most celebrated persons of each family |publisher=J. Nichols |year=1817 |pages=271–2 |chapterurl=https://books.google.ie/books?id=taIBAAAAYAAJ&&pg=PA271 |chapter=Hayes St. Leger, Viscount Doneraile}}</ref> Through his mother, he was a grandson of [[Arthur St Leger, 1st Viscount Doneraile]].<ref name="Brydges1817p271"/> 

He was given the name of St Leger Aldworth at birth, but he legally changed his surname to St Leger on 9 May 1767,{{cn|date=January 2016}} when he succeeded to the Doneraile estates upon the death of his uncle, Hayes St Leger, 4th Viscount Doneraile (1702–1767).<ref name="Brydges1817p271"/> Like several other members of his family, he served in the [[Irish House of Commons]] as the Member of Parliament for [[Doneraile (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Doneraile]], sitting between 1749 and 1776.<ref name="Brydges1817p271"/> 

On 2 July 1776, St Leger was created '''Baron Doneraile''' in the [[Peerage of Ireland]].<ref name="Brydges1817p271"/> On 5 January 1785, he was created '''Viscount Doneraile''', of Doneraile in County Cork, the title previously held by his maternal relations.<ref name="Brydges1817p271"/>

==Marriage, children and succession==
He married Mary Barry, the daughter of Redmond Barry, and together they had six children, including Hayes St Leger, 2nd Viscount. 

